    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Oil Pan and Oil Suction Tube -
        Removal - Oil Pan and Gasket
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pan and Gasket</title>
        <figure id="f3350011274" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk06/K06006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pan bolts and rail stiffeners</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 24 bolt (18)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan rail stiffener (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan end rail stiffener (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1102" count="1">Remove 18 M8 x 24 oil pan mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two oil pan end rail stiffeners and two oil pan rail stiffeners.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate oil pan from the oil pan gasket and remove oil pan from engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350011275" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK06/K06007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pan gasket, RTV sealant locations, and suction tube assembly (front sump)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">RTV sealant locations</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 25 bolt (front sump)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pan gasket dowel (into crankcase)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 35 bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The oil pan gasket is reusable if it is not cracked and the sealing surface is in good
                    condition.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil pan gasket from the front cover, flywheel housing, and crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut through RTV sealant under the oil pan gasket at locations on the oil pan mounting
                surface using a flat gasket scraper or similar tool. Cut parallel to the gasket path.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
